title._content: Barstow, Zedekiah S. of Keene New Hampshire

description._content: TITLE Barstow, Zedekiah S. of Keene New Hampshire CREATOR French, J.A., Keene NH SUBJECT Clergy - NH - Keene Men - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Stereograph of Zedekiah Smith Barstow of Keene New Hampshire. Zedekiah was born in 1790 in Canterbury CT and died in Keene in 1873. Dr. Barstow graduated from Yale and Dartmouth and was ordained in 1818. He started the Cheshire Theological Institute and was the last minister settled by the town before the separation of civil and church authority. He officiated until he was 80 years old. He was married to Elizabeth Fay Blake. PUBLISHER Keene Public Library and the Historical Society of Cheshire County DATE DIGITAL 20091120 DATE ORIGINAL 1868 RESOURCE TYPE stereographs FORMAT image/jpg RESOURCE IDENTIFIER HS304-P2386 RIGHTS MANAGMENT No known copyright restrictions.
